The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Chennai, May 26 (PTI): The Tamil Nadu police today detained 96 people and stepped up search operations across the state following the theft of 17,100 detonators from a private godown near Tiruchirappalli.           
	The police have sounded a statewide alert with the focus on coastal districts and are investigating the involvement of a Sri Lankan militant group. On Sunday, the owner of the godown found the door of one of the chambers broken open and many detonators missing. The detonators are used for quarrying.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): A bank cannot be asked to pay the amount on a misplaced cheque unless it is proved that the cheque has been encashed by a third person, the Delhi consumer commission said.           an appeal from the Central Bank of India, the commission set aside a district forum order to the bank to credit Rs 72,175, the amount on three cheques misplaced by it, to a complainants account. However, it ordered the bank to pay compensation to the complainant, holding misplacing of cheques as deficiency in service.                  
	 Bharatpur (PTI): An Islamic cleric has been detained for interrogation in connection with the Jaipur serial blasts on May 13 that killed 67 people, police said on Monday. Mohamaad Ilyas, the imam of the Jama Masjid here, was detained on Friday and has been taken to Jaipur for questioning. A computer, mobile phone and diaries have been seized from him.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): Film financer and producer Jhamu Sugandh died of a massive cardiac arrest here on Monday. He was 57. Sugandh was involved in the making of movies like Lagaan, Hum Dil De Chuke Sanam and Rangeela.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Two minors were allegedly raped by persons known to them and a teenager was molested by her friend after she refused his proposal for marriage, police said on Monday. A 10-year-old girl was raped allegedly by her paternal uncle, and his son sexually assaulted her in her home in east Delhi. An 11-year-old girl was raped allegedly by her neighbour at his home in southwest Delhi.                                                                                                                         
